                <h2 style="font-family:Abel; color:cornflowerblue;text-align:center;">Sports Facilities</h2>

                <div class="clear" style="display: none;"></div>

                <h3>THE ROYAL BILLIARDS ROOM</h3>
                <img src="https://rgmc.in/wp-content/themes/rgmc/club/images/1.png" align="left">
                <p align="justify">The facility happens to be as old as the building. Initially, on the ground floor it was shifted to first floor in 1990s. There are three billiard/snooker tables and they are all crafted elegantly. Timing for members is from 02:00 p.m. to 10.00 p.m. and for dependents on table no. 2 in afternoon. The most honoured player who played has been Mr. Alok Kumar an Arjuna Awardee who participated in an invitation tournament organized by the club in 2010.</p>

                <div class="clear" style="display: none;"></div>

                <img src="https://rgmc.in/wp-content/themes/rgmc/club/images/2.png" align="left">
                <h3>FOUNTAIN OF HEALTH 'THE GYM'</h3>
                <p align="justify">Powered by equipment from most valued international brands, the fitness centre is truly 'state of the art' and guarantees the most refreshing experience like never before. We have a qualified trainer who helps every member in crafting a personalized module. In keeping with the trend, "fitness" being the Mantra of life for both young and old, GCE, Amritsar has provided best infrastructure at the most affordable cost one can dream of We promise a healthy and happy environment for those who crave for fitness in style. Timings are 05:30 a.m. to 09:00 a.m. (morning) and 04:00 p.m. to 08:30 p.m. (evening).</p>
                <div class="clear" style="display: none;"></div>

                <h3>THE JOGGING TRACK</h3>
                <img src="https://rgmc.in/wp-content/themes/rgmc/club/images/3.png" align="left">
                <p align="justify">Created in 1990s Jogging track is canopied by a variety of majestic flowering trees like gulmohar, amaltas, chakrasia, silver oak, silver palm etc. Its all 750 meters take you through most pictorious flower valley and other green belts of RGMC. The concept of piped music has been recently added and being appreciated by nature lovers and joggers alike.</p>

                <div class="clear" style="display: none;"></div>
                <h3>BADMINTON HALL</h3>
                <img src="https://rgmc.in/wp-content/themes/rgmc/club/images/4.png" align="left">
                <p align="justify">The hall was built in year 2001 at shoe string budget under watchful supervision of Chief National Coach Mr. T.P.S. Puri and International player Mr. Vinod Vatrana. The hall is built as per international standards and houses two courts with wooden flooring. Coaching facility for children is available at fixed hours. It was inaugurated by Asian Champion and Arjuna Awardee Mr. Dinesh Khanna who also played the first game on it on 27th May 2001. Timings are 05:30 a.m. to 08:30 a.m. (morning) and 04:00 p.m. to 09:00 p.m. (evening).</p>
                <div class="clear" style="display: none;"></div>

                <h3>TABLE TENNIS</h3>
                <img src="https://rgmc.in/wp-content/themes/rgmc/club/images/5.png" align="left">
                <p align="justify">An ultra modern Table Tennis hall was built in 2012 in memory of Dr. Bipin Saronwala. Synthetic flooring and air conditioning are its hallmark. It is the most prestigious addition to the RGMC sports facility and inaugurated with an invitation match by International Table Tennis star Mr. Kamlesh Mehta and other national players. Timings are 06:00 a.m. to 09:00 a.m. (morning) and 04:00 p.m. to 08:00 p.m. (evening).</p>

                <div class="clear" style="display: none;"></div>

                <h3>VOLLEYBALL</h3>
                <img src="https://rgmc.in/wp-content/themes/rgmc/club/images/6.png" align="left">
                <p align="justify">Volleyball is a truly outdoor game and the ultimate test of physical and mental fitness. On demand of members it was initiated in 2005 as a club game. It has been upgraded to two courts with appropriate fencing. Timings are 05:30 a.m. to 09:00 a.m. (morning) and 04:00 p.m. to 07:30 p.m. (evening).</p>

                <div class="clear" style="display: none;"></div>

                <h3>LAWN TENNIS</h3>
                <img src="https://rgmc.in/wp-content/themes/rgmc/club/images/7.png" align="left">
                <p align="justify">Been to Rolland Garros for French Open? Not needed! A visit to red clay topped tennis courts of RGMC will suffice. Tennis as sports facility came up as one of the first few facilities when the club was initiated. Initially there were eight grass courts and only four were used at a time. Gradually, considering the difficulty of maintaining the grass courts the management in 1980-1990s converted then into three gravel courts and one hard court. In 2004, it was decided to build four red clay courts designed by experts. At present it caters to a large number of members and their children. The courts are flood lit and have hosted several national and inter club tournaments. Regular coaching has ensured that many children from here have attained national level in this sports. Timings are 05:30 a.m. to 09:00 a.m. (morning) and 03:00 p.m. to 07:30 p.m. (evening).</p>

                <div class="clear" style="display: none;"></div>
                <h3>THE CARD ROOM</h3>
                <img src="https://rgmc.in/wp-content/themes/rgmc/club/images/8.png" align="left">
                <p align="justify">Normal opening hours are from 12:00 p.m. to 10:00 p.m. Members are, however, permitted to play for an additional hour on due payment. The game of Rummy and Bridge are allowed and they are played in accordance with the "Law of Rummy and Bridge". Only low stakes are permitted. Several senior citizens avail of this facility for recreation.</p>

                <div class="clear" style="display: none;"></div>


                <h3>SWIMMING POOL</h3>
                <img src="https://rgmc.in/wp-content/themes/rgmc/club/images/9.png" align="left">
                <p align="justify">It is one of the oldest facility of the club, reminiscent of the colonial era. It caters to about 300 members in summers on any given day. It was renovated to its current shape in 1980s when a children pool was also added. The new addition (2013) is a small pool side gym. Timings are from 05:30 a.m. to 09:00 a.m. (morning) and from 04:30 p.m. to 09:00 p.m.</p>

                <div class="clear" style="display: none;"></div>



                <h3>SQUASH</h3>
                <img src="https://rgmc.in/wp-content/themes/rgmc/club/images/10.png" align="left">
                <p align="justify">Built in 1890's under the patronage of Maharaja Rajindra Singh Ji, it is one of the oldest squash courts in the country. Artisans who built it included wood craft experts from Peking (China). It has played host to several international and national players. Timings are from 05:00 a.m. to 08:30 a.m. (morning) and 05:00 p.m. to 09:00 p.m. (evening).</p>
                <div class="clear" style="display: none;"></div>

                <h3>Rules and regulations for sports facilities:</h3>

                <p align="justify"><img src="https://rgmc.in/wp-content/themes/rgmc/images/check1.png" class="aa">All sports facilities are closed on Monday.</p>
                <p align="justify"><img src="https://rgmc.in/wp-content/themes/rgmc/images/check1.png" class="aa">Dress code is a must.</p>
                <p align="justify"><img src="https://rgmc.in/wp-content/themes/rgmc/images/check1.png" class="aa">Coaches are available in almost all facilities and they are also the supervisors for conducting the game and for the sports register.</p>
                <p align="justify"><img src="https://rgmc.in/wp-content/themes/rgmc/images/check1.png" class="aa">Hard drinks and major course meals are not permitted in sports facilities.</p>
                <p align="justify"><img src="https://rgmc.in/wp-content/themes/rgmc/images/check1.png" class="aa">Regular sports charges are Rs. 300-400 per month. Guest charges are applicable as per rules.</p>

            </div>





